webwork.pg-code:
Context()->variables->add(t=>"Real");
$a = Compute("2.8*e**(0.85)")->with(
  tolType => 'absolute',
  tolerance => .0051,
);
$percent = Compute("(e**0.85-1)*100")->with(
  tolType => 'absolute',
  tolerance => .51,
);
$b = Formula("2.8*(1+$percent/100)**t");

solution.p:
For this decay law, N_0 = 60 and b = 0.8. We would like to find a value for k so that e^k = b = 0.8, that is, we must solve the equation
		e^k \amp = 0.8\amp\amp \blert{\text{Take natural log of both sides.}}
		  \ln {(e^k)}\amp = \ln {(0.8)}\amp\amp \blert{\text{Simplify.}}
		  k\amp = \ln {(0.8)} \approx -0.2231
Replacing b with e^k, we find that the decay law is
		N(t) \approx 60e^{-0.2231t}

